SIMPLE: permission
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Permission
<hw>Per*mis"sion</hw> <pr>(p⟦etil⟧r*m⟦icr⟧sh"⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>permissio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>permission</ets>. See
<er>Permit</er>.]</ety> <def>The act of permitting or allowing; formal
consent; authorization; leave; license or liberty granted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>High <qex>permission</qex> of all-ruling Heaven.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You have given me your <qex>permission</qex> for this address.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Leave; liberty; license.</syn> <usage> --
<er>Leave</er>, <er>Permission</er>. <xex>Leave</xex> implies that the
recipient may decide whether to use the license granted or not.
<xex>Permission</xex> is the absence on the part of another of anything
preventive, and in general, at least by implication, signifies
approval.</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Permissive</ent>⟦br⟧
